title: Mission Description
content: Just when an exhilarating new adventure was about to begin, I'm suddenly hit with some mystery illness... Wait, no, I got sick, and even fell into a coma!?When I finally came to, what I saw nearly knocked me off my feet — a bizarre, psychedelic world of mind, with hissed demonic whispers. Could this be......No, I have no clue at all! Come to think of it... am I even really awake?

speaker: March 7th
line: (Cold... it's freezing...)

speaker: March 7th
line: (Hold on... am I dreaming? This is way too strange...)

speaker: March 7th
line: Ugh, everything's spinning... And I can see Wubbaboos flying around...

speaker: March 7th
line: But I was literally just talking to Himeko ! How did I... when did I...?

speaker: March 7th
line: ▶ That's it! ( Trailblazer ) warned me about this place , right before Qlipoth glimpsed ( him... / her... )

speaker: March 7th
line: Oh no... Have I accidentally walked onto some weird Path ?

speaker: March 7th
line: Have I done something crazy without remembering? Unless forcing Pom-Pom into new outfits and borrowing Mr. Yang 's shoulder massager counts...

speaker: March 7th
line: Hold up— Aha ? No way! Stepping onto the Path of Elation can't be this simple... right?

speaker: Voice of the Path
line: Child of Remembrance ...

speaker: Voice of the Path
line: Step forth... into the depths of the Path Space...

speaker: March 7th
line: Who's... who's there!?

speaker: March 7th
line: H—Hey, cut it out! If you're there, just... come out and talk, okay? You're freaking me out... I can't even think straight!

speaker: March 7th
line: Hold on... is that a gate?

speaker: Voice of the Path
line: Cast aside your fears...

speaker: Voice of the Path
line: Step forward... through the Gate of Memory...

speaker: March 7th
line: The voice... is it showing me the way out?

text: Pass through the Gate of Memory

line: Oh no, don't fall for it...
They're lying to you, turn back now...

speaker: March 7th
line: Another voice... who now?

speaker: March 7th
line: Wait... Master Diviner? From the Luofu ?

speaker: March 7th
line: Fu... I mean, Master Diviner, what brings you here?

speaker: March 7th
line: And you, Miss Messenger... do I know you from somewhere?

speaker: "Fu Xuan"
line: Good to see you again, March.

speaker: Messenger
line: A pleasure to see you, Miss March.

speaker: March 7th
line: That's it... Master Diviner used the Matrix of Prescience to help me search for my memories...

speaker: March 7th
line: And you, Miss Messenger... we met in that memory space. You said to me—

speaker: March 7th
line: "The value of your life does not lie in what happened in the past, but in the present, and the future."

speaker: Messenger
line: Your memory serves you well.

speaker: "Fu Xuan"
line: March, I conducted some experiments with the Six-Phased Ice you left us.

speaker: "Fu Xuan"
line: Thanks to the Garden of Recollection , the Matrix of Prescience has made a breakthrough in extrapolating the past. Now, we might be able to bypass the obstacles and look directly into your history.

speaker: Messenger
line: The Master Diviner is right. Continue down this Path, and you'll be able to find your lost "memories" at the end.

speaker: Messenger
line: Since we last met, you've grown much alongside the Trailblaze. You should be strong enough now to bear the weight of your past.

speaker: March 7th
line: Well, there goes my ice princess fairy tale...

speaker: March 7th
line: I need to know... Master Diviner, Miss Messenger, this isn't just another dream, is it?

speaker: March 7th
line: If this is real, why reach out to me at this exact moment?

speaker: "Fu Xuan"
line: The situation is... dire. Your lost memories... they're crucial to the Garden of Recollection.

speaker: Messenger
line: She's right. The Garden of Recollection's existence hangs on your memories.

speaker: March 7th
line: The Garden... of Recollection...

speaker: Messenger
line: You may not want to sacrifice anything to preserve the Garden for now, but in time, you'll understand... your destiny and the Path of Remembrance are extremely closely intertwined.

speaker: Messenger
line: Now go.

speaker: March 7th
line: So I just... walk through that gate?

speaker: "Fu Xuan"
line: This way, March. Your past awaits beyond the Gate of Memory.
Stop! They're just mimicking people from your memories...

speaker: March 7th
line: That voice again...
Don't let those bad people deceive you...

speaker: March 7th
line: The gate... it moved? Where's the master diviner?

speaker: March 7th
line: ▶ Now it's... Dan Heng and (Trailblazer)?

speaker: March 7th
line: Hey guys... what are you doing in a place like this?

speaker: Dan Heng
line: March! There you are...

speaker: (Trailblazer)
line: ▶ ...finally.

speaker: Dan Heng
line: The Trailblazing journey just isn't the same without you.

speaker: (Trailblazer)
line: ▶ Traveling's no fun without you around.

speaker: March 7th
line: Well duh! What's Team Trailblaze without its star member?

speaker: March 7th
line: ▶ Wait a second... You might look like (Trailblazer) and Dan Heng, but...

speaker: Dan Heng
line: We understand your confusion. The Garden's allies helped us establish this neural link to reach you.

speaker: March 7th
line: The Garden's allies... you mean Miss Black Swan?

speaker: Dan Heng
line: Yes, she helped make this possible.

speaker: (Trailblazer)
line: ▶ Keep going, March.

speaker: (Trailblazer)
line: ▶ Find your past, wake up... and travel with us again.

speaker: March 7th
line: That sounds... really tempting. Finding my past and continuing to trailblaze new worlds with you...

speaker: Dan Heng
line: Trust in yourself, March. It's gotten us this far, hasn't it?

speaker: Dan Heng
line: Follow us. Let's go through that gate together.

text: Follow your friends to pass through the Gate of Memory

speaker: Dan Heng
line: Step into your past, March...

speaker: Dan Heng
line: Find your true self.

text: Pass through the Gate of Memory

line: Wait up! Slow down...
Those words sound so sweet...
But keep your eyes open, don't let them fool you.
Whew... at last... I finally caught up.

speaker: March 7th
line: Hey... are you alright?
I'll be... okay... just not used to... running around...
Say, March? Got a moment to talk before you make your decision?

speaker: March 7th
line: Wait, that was you? Pushing the gate away, sending those warnings?

speaker: Cyrene
line: Yep! Name's Cyrene — it means "ripples of past reverie"... Easy to remember, right?

speaker: Cyrene
line: Wait a minute... we actually look quite alike, don't we?

speaker: March 7th
line: Yeah! Your pink hair is just as eye-catching as mine!

speaker: Cyrene
line: And we're both bright, pretty, and positive girls! Talk about coincidence!

speaker: March 7th
line: Wow, you're quite the smooth talker... but I can't disagree!

speaker: March 7th
line: Wait, you know my name is March? Have we met?

speaker: Cyrene
line: No, but I've witnessed your story through those memories just now.

speaker: Cyrene
line: It's incredible, really. We might have more in common than you think... I know exactly what you're going through, which is why I don't want to see you exploited or hurt.

speaker: March 7th
line: You know what I'm going through?

speaker: Cyrene
line: I know because I've been exactly where you are.

speaker: Cyrene
line: This empty space has been my home for ages... I barely remember what time feels like anymore.

speaker: Cyrene
line: But there's something I'll never forget.

speaker: Cyrene
line: Trust me, that gate won't give you what you want.

speaker: March 7th
line: You mean those people, they're lying? Luring me into a trap?

speaker: Cyrene
line: Yes. Convincing, weren't they? They've studied your memories, using your deepest wishes against you. How dare they manipulate a young girl's feelings like that.

speaker: Cyrene
line: If you go through that door, the worst case scenario is you'll become their pawn, losing control over your own fate forever.

speaker: March 7th
line: You've seen what's on the other side?

speaker: Cyrene
line: I may be stuck here with missing memories like you, but I still recall fragments of my homeland where I grew up...

speaker: Cyrene
line: That door leads to Amphoreus . Trust me, it's anything but welcoming.

speaker: Cyrene
line: For ages, I've watched people walk through that door. They couldn't see or hear my calls. The voices beyond always promised safety, but I've never seen anyone return safely...

speaker: Cyrene
line: So I had to try and stop you.

speaker: March 7th
line: To be honest, I'm not sure what to believe. But the fact that you're here, putting in all this effort to warn me... that means something.

speaker: March 7th
line: Tell me, Cyrene, how can I return to my world?

speaker: Cyrene
line: It's really easy, actually. Just turn around and walk away from this place.

speaker: Memokeeper's Embodiment
line: The girl... cannot be trusted...

speaker: Memokeeper's Embodiment
line: Through the door... save... the Garden...

speaker: Memokeeper's Embodiment
line: Both of you... children of Remembrance...

speaker: Cyrene
line: They never give up, do they? But don't let them sway you. Stick to your path.

speaker: Cyrene
line: The return journey could take ages... longer than most lives...

speaker: Cyrene
line: But that path will lead you home.

speaker: March 7th
line: Thank you, Cyrene. I know what I need to do!

speaker: March 7th
line: I'm going through that gate, into Amphoreus.

speaker: Cyrene
line: Wait, what...?

speaker: March 7th
line: Don't worry, I believe you. It's just that for me, the only place I can call "home"...

speaker: March 7th
line: ...is right beside my friends.

speaker: March 7th
line: Two of my closest friends are already on their way to Amphoreus. They may seem capable, but only I know...

speaker: March 7th
line: They're absolute disasters waiting to happen! They won't last five minutes in a new world without me!

speaker: March 7th
line: That's why I need to go through... Amphoreus or not. When the three of us are together, there's nothing we can't handle.

speaker: March 7th
line: We'll explore, understand, establish, and connect — after that, we'll find our way home together!

speaker: Cyrene
line: ...I see. You've got people who mean the world to you too.

speaker: Cyrene
line: That's so heartwarming! March, if that's what you've decided, you have my full support.

speaker: Cyrene
line: Birds of a feather we are! Looking all sweet and innocent, but with hearts of fire!

speaker: March 7th
line: ...Oh stop, you're making me blush!

speaker: March 7th
line: Well then, I guess this is it.

speaker: March 7th
line: Do you think... we'll see each other again?

speaker: Cyrene
line: Who knows!

speaker: Cyrene
line: But don't worry about me! After all this time here, I've grown quite used to chatting with my imaginary friends.

speaker: March 7th
line: Since Amphoreus is your homeland... if there's a way to help you, my companions and I will do everything we can.

speaker: Cyrene
line: Then I'll look forward to that day!

speaker: Cyrene
line: Your story awaits, March. Make it an epic one♪
